<subSubSection id="A8B7C4FE5252839E0A4FFAF588F638DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="003995DF6CEA5AEF33864DF7BD976F20" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="001C039784CF97F5E0DB2C4F465B4F6C" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Based on the molecular phylogeny, 
<taxonomicName id="FB34F11BE0553F0289438A0FAEFAF97F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. fanii" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fanii">
<emphasis id="B3CEC67D5133BD73CF4099714DBFBE90" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">L. fanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="12BF38516D66866D320D0C0020F45A86" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Idiophyton">Idiophyton</taxonomicName>
, that is also supported by the morphological characters of basifixed anthers, short filaments and anthers open by apical pores. 
<taxonomicName id="765DD1AB3D94AB46F27780D1C930B8B2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. fanii" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fanii">
<emphasis id="6C769F18600475646C4C9C706786E368" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">L. fanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="5E2145F000BBB70F162FDA23237AA30E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. verbascifolia" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verbascifolia">
<emphasis id="3A56BBD1933BDA366922F61CB9C1A363" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">L. verbascifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C.M.Hu &amp; L.K.Phan that is endemic to limestone areas in Vietnam (
<bibRefCitation id="A7BE28E09DC04C62198D96065306B07A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.2011.01174.x" author="Phan, KL" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="601 - 604" refId="B14" refString="Phan, KL, Hu, CM, 2011. Lysimachia vietnamensis and L. verbascifolia spp. nov. (Primulaceae) from Vietnam. Nordic Journal of Botany 29 (5): 601 - 604, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.2011.01174.x" title="Lysimachia vietnamensis and L. verbascifolia spp. nov. (Primulaceae) from Vietnam." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.2011.01174.x" volume="29" year="2011">Phan and Hu 2011</bibRefCitation>
), but can be easily distinguished by its spatulate to narrowly oblanceolate leaf blade and glabrous adaxially and glandular abaxially. 
<taxonomicName id="BC1EDBE849C6AC325BB75F96B1FE8CE3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. fanii" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fanii">
<emphasis id="89F9550AF2C2B69A86F15CBEBE87C1CA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">L. fanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9A0269A649E7B3EFCA1D3E0D1F4762E9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. alpestris" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpestris">
<emphasis id="CD360F3B1E1D8E461AD6F975F34D4AD0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">L. alpestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Champ. ex Benth. resemble each other in having congested leaves and spatulate to narrowly oblanceolate leaf blades and invisible veins and solitary inflorescences but 
<taxonomicName id="3588085EC7E51D3EB935786DD80AAA71" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. fanii" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fanii">
<emphasis id="63022DB808A64FA5B5E6B246B300E619" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">L. fanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="AB639787903725799278B25E641DC8EB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. alpestris" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpestris">
<emphasis id="E65644142D25F53F87B330F7CF3E238D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">L. alpestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its rhizome which is branched at the apex without stolons from the base, leaf blade glabrous adaxially and glandular abaxially, basifixed anthers which open by apical pores. 
<taxonomicName id="2C17E8303D79994A2E74FB6C13BCAD35" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. fanii" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fanii">
<emphasis id="CEF892BB01DC27561DF50E9E9F3B89E7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">L. fanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0334ECB2733458B0D5A307D2DCF551C7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. rupestris" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rupestris">
<emphasis id="F371FA5D0C0F89A2CC1E4C3C81E8BE97" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">L. rupestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
F.H.Chen &amp; C.M.Hu from limestone areas distributed in south-western China and northern Vietnam (
<bibRefCitation id="90099060808F121BE7FD7C46BD1D46A0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5252/a2017n2a3" author="Tong, YH" journalOrPublisher="Adansonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="125 - 128" refId="B18" refString="Tong, YH, Xia, NH, Lam, LV, 2017. Lysimachia rupestris F.H.Chen &amp; C.M.Hu (Primulaceae): A new record for the flora of Vietnam and reconsideration of its taxonomical position. Adansonia 39 (2): 125 - 128, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5252/a2017n2a3" title="Lysimachia rupestris F. H. Chen &amp; C. M. Hu (Primulaceae): A new record for the flora of Vietnam and reconsideration of its taxonomical position." url="https://doi.org/10.5252/a2017n2a3" volume="39" year="2017">Tong et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
), but it can be distinguished from the latter by its rhizome which is branched at the apex and without stolons from the base, leaf blade spatulate to narrowly oblanceolate and glabrous adaxially, lateral veins invisible on both sides. A comparison of the main characters of the four species is shown in Table 
<tableCitation id="B125AF7002316EB57E9B109523BB03E3" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T2" captionText="Table 2. Comparison of characters amongst Lysimachia fanii, L. verbascifolia, L. rupestris and L. alpestris." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/4E52EB8C138E44B3334BC67986D9DE26" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" tableUuid="4E52EB8C138E44B3334BC67986D9DE26">2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
